<br>
As for chanters soloing with a pet and rune line, that is a viable option as well. Although I consider even rune III to be too pricy. I prefer to use the beserker line. Plain and simple, it's free. <br>
<br>
Oh and another tip for pet soloer's, If you really want your under armored, under healthed pet to truly lay waste about it, then go out and buy a bunch of gnoll hide lariets. Hand two of them to your pet, and watch the fun. Supposedly unlike magician pets, enchanter pets will not deal out duel weild damage unless you have a weapon to give to it, and buying some cheap proc weapons is much better than buying a FS sword in Cobalt scar because you don't have anything else. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  A level 49 pet, with Swift, beserker str, Shadow, 2 Lariets, and good use of fear, can kill wyverns all day long. <p>Slymie Ras <br>
